<title type="html"><![CDATA[Retrofit RF wireless tech into old IR systems -NES Satellite]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7352&amp;p=72330#p72330"><![CDATA[
If i'm thinking correctly I dont need controllers at all, they already exist in the satellite transmitter and reciever. Already pulled some datasheets for some of the chips in each module, trans has a tmp42c70 and the reciever has a tmp42c60p, both 4bit mirco-controllers. What i'm saying is the satellite already has "protocol" in place for communicating, I just want to change the method (from IR to RF) not the language it uses to communicate.<br />I'm starting to wonder if those need to be dumped in order to be sure of what pins are used for data in/out. Maybe just retracing the IR LEDs traces will lead me to the right pin?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4082">akaviolence</a> — Tue Jan 04, 2011 7:43 pm</p><hr />
